  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The SOFA score is a severity of illness and prognostic score used in the ICU. It has also
      recently been adopted as part of the definition of sepsis. This study will prospectively
      evaluate the usability of automated SOFA scoring for ICU patients within an electronic
      patient monitoring dashboard. It will also assess for changes in physician ordering (volume
      and types of orders) after automatic scoring is implemented.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
